      "content": "The solution is not a simple \"yes\" or \"no,\" but rather a matter of political will to design the system correctly. A successful implementation requires robust revenue recycling, where the collected fees are directly reinvested into public transit improvements and subsidies for low-income residents. If the revenue is used to fund better, more affordable alternatives, it mitigates the burden on the working class. Without that strong equity component, the system is indeed politically and socially fragile.",
