      "content": "that makes sense. but some people argue that even with transit improvements, it's still just an extra cost for people who have no choice but to drive, like tradespeople or delivery drivers. they see it more as a \"war on drivers\" than a climate fix. do you think those concerns are valid, or are they just being used to block progress on climate goals?",
