      "content": "Those concerns are entirely valid because they highlight the reality of essential workers whose jobs are tied to driving within city limits. Framing it as a \"war on drivers\" is a potent political tactic used to derail necessary climate action. The focus needs to shift from punishing drivers to incentivizing behavioral change through superior public options. Therefore, the policy must include targeted exemptions or significant discounts for commercial and essential service vehicles.",
      "source": "target",
